description: Number of primes less than square root of n-th prime; i.e. number of trial divisions by smaller primes to show that n-th prime is indeed prime.
links: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: a(32) = 5 since the 32nd prime is 131 which is not divisible by 2, 3, 5, 7 or 11 (and does not need to be tested against 13, 17, 19 etc. since 13^2 = 169>131).
maple: a:= proc(n) option remember;      numtheory[pi] (floor (sqrt (ithprime(n))))    end:seq (a(n), n=1..100);  # _Alois P. Heinz_, Sep 05 2011
author: _Henry Bottomley_, Jan 29 2001
